'''Jan-Frederik Uys''' (born {{birth date|1994|01|03|df=y}} in [[Potchefstroom]], [[South Africa]]) is a South African [[rugby union]] player, currently playing with the {{Rut Eastern Province Kings}}.<ref name="SARU Player Profile Jan Uys">{{cite web | url=http://www.sarugby.net/playerprofile.aspx?id=51296 | title=SARU Player Profile Jan Uys | work=South African Rugby Union | accessdate=6 November 2014}}</ref> His regular position is lock.

==Career==

===Youth and Varsity Cup rugby===

He attended and played high school rugby for [[Paul Roos Gymnasium]] in [[Stellenbosch]]. This led to his selection in the Western Province side that played at the Under-16 Grant Khomo Week in [[Upington]] in 2010. This, in turn, earned him an inclusion in a South African Under-16 High Performance squad that attended a training camp in [[Cape Town]].<ref name="SA U16 High Performance squad">{{cite web | url=http://www.supersport.com/rugby/junior-rugby/news/100803/SA_U16_High_Performance_squad | title=SA U16 High Performance squad | publisher=SuperSport | date=3 August 2010 | accessdate=6 November 2014}}</ref> In 2011, Uys represented the Western Province Under-18 side that played at the Academy Week tournament.

He joined the Western Province Rugby Institute after high school and played for the {{Rut Western Province U19}} team that played in the [[2013 Under-19 Provincial Championship]].

In 2014, he played in the first five matches of the {{Rut UCT Ikey Tigers}}' [[2014 Varsity Rugby#Varsity Cup|2014 Varsity Cup]], a competition that UCT went on to win, beating the {{Rut NWU Pukke}} in the final.<ref name="Match Breakdown: FNB NWU-PUKKE vs FNB UCT 1ST XV">{{cite web | url=http://www.sarugby.net/matchbreakdown.aspx?id=117324&category=&leagueid=1694&homeid=17224&awayid=17214&fullview=true | title=Match Breakdown: FNB NWU-PUKKE vs FNB UCT 1ST XV | work=South African Rugby Union | date=7 April 2014 | accessdate=8 April 2014}}</ref> After a stint playing [[Vodacom Cup]] rugby (see [[Jan Uys#Western Province|below]], Uys played a big part in the {{Rut Western Province U21}} side's [[2014 Under-21 Provincial Championship]] campaign. He made eight appearances during the season to help them finish top of the log and subsequently reach the final of the tournament. He played in the final, but could not prevent his side losing the final 20<U+2013>10 to the {{Rut Blue Bulls U21}}s on home soil.<ref name="Blue Bulls crowned champions in Absa Under-21 final">{{cite web | url=http://www.sarugby.net/article.aspx?category=sarugby/juniorprovincial&id=2700004 | title=Blue Bulls crowned champions in Absa Under-21 final | publisher=South African Rugby Union | date=25 October 2014 | accessdate=28 October 2014}}</ref><ref name="Match Breakdown: Western Province U21 vs Blue Bulls U21 (final)">{{cite web | url=http://www.sarugby.net/matchbreakdown.aspx?id=121164&category=&leagueid=1834&homeid=18474&awayid=18454&fullview=true | title=Match Breakdown: Western Province U21 vs Blue Bulls U21 | work=South African Rugby Union | date=25 October 2014 | accessdate=28 October 2014}}</ref>

===Western Province===

Uys made his first class debut during the [[2014 Vodacom Cup]] competition. He started {{Rut Western Province}}'s opening match of the season, a 16<U+2013>8 victory over near-neighbours {{Rut Boland Cavaliers}}.<ref name="Match Breakdown: DHL Western Province vs Regent Boland Cavaliers">{{cite web | url=http://www.sarugby.net/matchbreakdown.aspx?id=117794&category=&leagueid=1734&homeid=17604&awayid=17534&fullview=true | title=Match Breakdown: DHL Western Province vs Regent Boland Cavaliers | work=South African Rugby Union | date=8 March 2014 | accessdate=6 November 2014}}</ref> He made five consecutive starts for Western Province at the start of the competition and played off the bench in the final two matches of the group stages of the competition. He also came on as a substitute in their Quarter Final match against the {{Rut Pumas}}, which ended in a 13<U+2013>8 victory for the [[Nelspruit]]-based side to see Western Province eliminated from the competition.<ref name="Match Breakdown: Steval Pumas vs DHL Western Province">{{cite web | url=http://www.sarugby.net/matchbreakdown.aspx?id=118284&category=&leagueid=1734&homeid=17524&awayid=17604&fullview=true | title=Match Breakdown: Steval Pumas vs DHL Western Province | work=South African Rugby Union | date=2 May 2014 | accessdate=6 November 2014}}</ref>

===Eastern Province Kings===

He then moved from the [[Western Cape]] to the [[Eastern Cape]], joining [[Port Elizabeth]]-based side the {{Rut Eastern Province Kings}} for the 2015 season.<ref name="EP Kings Pre Season Training Squad announcedee">{{cite web | url=http://www.rugby15.co.za/2014/11/ep-kings-pre-season-training-squad-announcedee/ | title=EP Kings Pre Season Training Squad announcedee | publisher=Rugby15 | date=5 November 2014 | accessdate=5 November 2014}}</ref>

